import React from 'react';
import '../../App.css';
import { Card, CardGroup } from 'react-bootstrap';


export default function Services() {
    return (
    
    <CardGroup>
    <Card>
      <Card.Img variant="top" src="images/PARIS.jpg" />
      <Card.Body>
        <Card.Title>PARIS</Card.Title>
        <Card.Text>
        The mesmerizing wrought-iron spire of the Eiffel Tower piercing the skyline, the Arc de Triomphe guarding the most glamorous avenue, the Champs Elysees, the regal Notre Dame cathedral, 
        lamp lit bridges spanning the Seine and art nouveau cafes spilling onto wicker-chair-lined terraces. 
        </Card.Text>
      </Card.Body>
      <Card.Footer>
        <small className="text-muted">Now On Booking open</small>
      </Card.Footer>
    </Card>
    <Card>
      <Card.Img variant="top" src="holder.js/100px160" />
      <Card.Body>
        <Card.Title>Card title</Card.Title>
        <Card.Text>
          This card has supporting text below as a natural lead-in to additional
          content.{' '}
        </Card.Text>
      </Card.Body>
      <Card.Footer>
        <small className="text-muted">Last updated 3 mins ago</small>
      </Card.Footer>
    </Card>
    <Card>
      <Card.Img variant="top" src="holder.js/100px160" />
      <Card.Body>
        <Card.Title>Card title</Card.Title>
        <Card.Text>
          This is a wider card with supporting text below as a natural lead-in to
          additional content. This card has even longer content than the first to
          show that equal height action.
        </Card.Text>
      </Card.Body>
      <Card.Footer>
        <small className="text-muted">Last updated 3 mins ago</small>
      </Card.Footer>
    </Card>
  </CardGroup>);
}
